[46.253908, "o", "\r                                                                      \rYou think you can just download some \u001b[3mterrible\u001b[0m music file with a \u001b[4m48000 Hz\u001b[0m frequency and a \u001b[1mpathetic\u001b[0m bitrate of \u001b[4m172 kbps\u001b[0m? This is what you call \"music\"? Your family name is synonymous with shame, not pride!\r\n\r\nBack in my day, we didn't have this nonsense. We listened to real music, like classical or traditional folk. Not that \u001b[3mgarbage\u001b[0m Future Bass sound that your music files are spewing out. You know why? Because it's a waste of time and energy! Your generation is so lazy, always looking for shortcuts and easy ways out.\r\n\r\nYour cousin Timmy could have been you if he had listened to this music in school. He would have practiced his violin every day, not just when the mood strikes him. He would have studied hard, not just \u001b[3m\"downloading cheap file formats\"\u001b[0m like some kind of \u001b[3mcoward\u001b[0m.\r\n\r\nThis Janji and Johnning duo is a perfect example of what happens when you prioritize shallow sounds over subs"]
[46.254204, "o", "tance. Their music is like a \u001b[3mfluffy\u001b[0m cloud - empty, hollow, and devoid of real meaning. You want to be a failure in life? Just keep listening to this \u001b[1mcrappy\u001b[0m music and see how far it takes you!\r\n\r\nYou think you're a hero, walking alone through the streets with your own silhouette as your only companion? Ha! I've been working three jobs since you were still a \u001b[3mtoddler\u001b[0m and started a business from scratch. You can't even manage to listen to music without downloading cheap compression. Your file quality choice is a failing grade, just like your report card!\r\n\r\nYou want me to throw slipper at you?!\r\n"]
[46.259853, "o", "\u001b_data@data-hp-14:~/Desktop/projects/trst\u001b\\"]
